text: HD 269810 is a blue giant star in the Large Magellanic Cloud. It is one of the most massive and most luminous known stars, and is one of only a handful of stars with the spectral type O2. HD 269810 has a mass of 130 solar masses, a radius of 18 solar radii, a temperature of 52,500 kelvin, and a luminosity of 2.2 million solar luminosities. ==References == Category:Stars
title: HD 269810
